Chap 2

Basic operations.

Create a vector in R. Print sentences and objects by function cat().

x = c(1,2,3)
y = c(4,5,6)
cat("x = ", x, "\n")
## x =  1 2 3
cat("y = ", y)
## y =  4 5 6

Do operations among vectors.

length(x)
## [1] 3
cat("x + y = ", x+y)
## x + y =  5 7 9

We can use function ls() to list all objects in this workspace. rm() can be used to remove objects you no longer need in this workspace.

ls()
## [1] "x" "y"
rm(x)
ls()
## [1] "y"
# Remove all objects.
rm(list = ls())
ls()
## character(0)

We can use function matrix() to create a matrix. And do some operations.

m = matrix(c(1,2,3,4),2,2,byrow=TRUE)
sqrt(m)
##          [,1]     [,2]
## [1,] 1.000000 1.414214
## [2,] 1.732051 2.000000
m^2
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]    1    4
## [2,]    9   16

We can create random variables, and use summary() to observe the information for this object.

set.seed(1303)
x=rnorm(50)
summary(x)
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
## -1.51032 -0.50842  0.02515  0.16955  0.68824  2.61575
y=x+rnorm(50,mean=50,sd=.1)
cat("\nMean of x is", mean(x),"\nvariance of x is", var(x),
    "\nstandard deviation is", sd(x),"\nsquare root of variance is",sqrt(var(x)), 
    "\ncorrelation of x and y is",cor(x,y))
## 
## Mean of x is 0.1695526 
## variance of x is 0.8013155 
## standard deviation is 0.8951623 
## square root of variance is 0.8951623 
## correlation of x and y is 0.9942128

Graphics.

plot(x,y,xlab="this is the x-axis",ylab="this is the y-axis",
main="Plot of X vs Y")

jpeg("Figure.pdf")
plot(x,y,col="green")
dev.off()
## png 
##   2
# We can create a sequence by function sep()
x=seq(-pi,pi,length=50)
y = x
f=outer(x,y,function(x,y)cos(y)/(1+x^2))
contour(x,y,f) # To plot explicitly, we need first run this line.
contour(x,y,f,nlevels=45,add=T)

fa=(f-t(f))/2 # t() means transpose here.
contour(x,y,fa,nlevels =15)

image(x,y,fa) # Heat map.

persp(x,y,fa)

persp(x,y,fa,theta=30)

persp(x,y,fa,theta=30,phi=20)

persp(x,y,fa,theta=30,phi=70)

persp(x,y,fa,theta=30,phi=40)

Indexing data.

A=matrix(1:16,4,4)
prmatrix(A)
##      [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
## [1,]    1    5    9   13
## [2,]    2    6   10   14
## [3,]    3    7   11   15
## [4,]    4    8   12   16
cat("\nA[2,3] is\n")
## 
## A[2,3] is
prmatrix(A[2,3])
##      [,1]
## [1,]   10
cat("\nA[c(1,3),c(2,4)] is\n")
## 
## A[c(1,3),c(2,4)] is
prmatrix(A[c(1,3),c(2,4)])
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]    5   13
## [2,]    7   15
cat("\nA[1:2,] is\n")
## 
## A[1:2,] is
prmatrix(A[1:2,])
##      [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
## [1,]    1    5    9   13
## [2,]    2    6   10   14
cat("\nA[,1:2] is\n")
## 
## A[,1:2] is
prmatrix(A[,1:2])
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]    1    5
## [2,]    2    6
## [3,]    3    7
## [4,]    4    8
cat("\nA[-c(1,3) ,] is\n")
## 
## A[-c(1,3) ,] is
prmatrix(A[-c(1,3) ,])
##      [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
## [1,]    2    6   10   14
## [2,]    4    8   12   16
cat("\ndim(A) is",dim(A))
## 
## dim(A) is 4 4

Loading data.

cur = getwd()
Auto=read.table(paste(cur,"/Datasets/Auto.data",sep = ""))
fix(Auto)
Auto=read.table(paste(cur,"/Datasets/Auto.data",sep = ""),header=T,na.strings ="?")
fix(Auto)
Auto=read.csv(paste(cur,"/Datasets/Auto.csv",sep = ""),header=T,na.strings ="?")
fix(Auto)

Additional Graphical and Numerical Summaries

plot(Auto$cylinders , Auto$mpg)

attach(Auto) # not suggested.
plot(cylinders , mpg)

cylinders =as.factor(cylinders ) # convert numerical vector into variable.
plot(cylinders , mpg)

plot(cylinders , mpg, col="red")

plot(cylinders , mpg, col="red", varwidth=T)

plot(cylinders , mpg, col="red", varwidth=T,horizontal =T)

plot(cylinders , mpg, col="red", varwidth=T, xlab="cylinders ",
ylab="MPG")

hist(mpg)

hist(mpg,col=2) # col = 2 equals to col = "red"

hist(mpg,col=2,breaks=15)
